Reasoning: The paper deals with the development of a behavioural theory for synchronous parallel algorithms, which involves the use of Abstract State Machines (ASMs) and finite model theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
